# Instinct RPG — Core card design (Annie’s preferences)

Use this when designing or reworking **Core** ability cards (creation picks, permanent Active-area
cards — Paladin **Oath**, Warlock **Patron**, etc.). Oath is the reference implementation; the same
principles apply to other dense Core layouts.

**Doctrine:** `design/paladin-oath-charge.md` · `design/card-anatomy.md` · `design/classes.md`  
**Builder:** `scripts/build_oath_html.py` · **Proof:** [paladin-oath-proof.html](https://elequin-sandbox.github.io/instinct-ttrpg/paladin-oath-proof.html)

---

## Workflow Annie expects

1. **Render before committing** — never describe a layout in prose and ask for approval. Build HTML,
   publish a proof page (`*-proof.html` or `*-layout-exploration.html`), link the **GitHub Pages URL**
   (`instinct-proof-links.mdc`).
2. **Side-by-side variants** when layout is in flux — same card, same rules, different structure
   (see `paladin-oath-layout-exploration.html`).
3. **Multiple-choice, one question at a time** when forks exist (`instinct-collaboration.mdc`).
4. **Agent runs the full pipeline** — builder → regen proof → patch `card-data.js` → Baserow push →
   commit + push `main` (`instinct-agent-ops.mdc`, `instinct-git.mdc`). Never hand scripts to Annie.

