## Oath vow block — canonical L→R mad-lib (“meet at *the*”)

**Player read:** place 2d6 in top slots → left die picks verb row, right die picks noun row → read
*Verb the Noun* left to right.

### Grid rule (critical)

Use **one shared CSS grid** for the dice row **and** all word rows.  
**Never** two separate grids with `1fr` columns — they compute different track widths and index chips
will **not** sit under die slots.

**5-column template:**

```
grid-template-columns: minmax(0,1fr) 22px minmax(26px,auto) 22px minmax(0,1fr);
```

| Col | Top row | Data rows |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | (empty) | verb — **right-aligned** toward center |
| 2 | left **die slot** (22px, centered) | left **index 1–6** (same 22px column) |
| 3 | ornate ***the*** (fleur-de-lis ring) | (empty spacer) |
| 4 | right **die slot** | right **index 1–6** |
| 5 | (empty) | noun — **left-aligned** toward center |

**Paired spines:** each die gets its **own** 1–6 column underneath — not a single center spine.

### Visual details Annie locked

- **Word-pool terms:** EB Garamond, **bold, not italic** (print readability).
- ***the* pivot:** italic inside golden oval ring with **⚜** caps (weighty center).
- **Index chips:** 22px-wide column, centered; match die column width.
- **Phrase frame:** dotted rounded border around the whole vow block.
- **No on-card subtitle** for Oath picks — flavor lives in doctrine / pool table only (reclaims header height).
- **Title bar:** class `hdr-bar` — rectangular (no clip-path swallowtail); `.hdr-title` one line, shrink in Card Studio.

### Body typography (post-header, Oath baseline)

| Element | Size |
|---|---|
| Effect text | 9px |
| Defiance / secondary | 8.5px |
| Vow terms | 9.5px bold |
| *the* in ring | 11.5px italic |
| Keyword pills | ~7.9px (`KW_SM`) |

Scale proportionally if Annie asks for ±5%; header ribbon stays unchanged.

