## On-card copy patterns (Oath — locked June 2026)

**Scene start:** `At **Scene start**: roll 2d6 to determine your new **Vow**:`

**Fulfill:**

> When an **Action** fulfills your **Vow**, add these dice to **Boost** the roll.

**Defiance** — **no subheader** (`Break Your Oath:` zone-label is retired on-card). Inline label in
uppercase tracked sans, same line as body:

> **Defiance:** Describe how you are defying your **Vow** and place these dice into your **Resolve**.
> The GM gains **Toll 2** to use against you.

Full procedure (once/scene, GM agrees, Boost 2 from both dice) stays in `design/paladin-oath-charge.md`
— on-card text is the **minimum**.

### Fixing idtag overlap

Preferred order:

1. **Shorter copy** / tighter wording  
2. **Manual `<br>`** to shorten the last line  
3. Slightly more `padding-bottom` on card-body  

**Avoid:** large `padding-left` indents on break text — Annie rejected that approach.

